The paper deals with the problem of designing interpretable voting classifiers without sacrificing accuracy. This is a problem that falls under the domain of machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary sub-discipline of the paper. The paper also deals with algorithms and experiments, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses theoretical results and approximation algorithms, which are covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper uses decision trees and boosting, which are common techniques in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
